tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE QuantumMetrics (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    protocol_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    transmission_rate FLOAT NOT NULL,
    error_rate FLOAT NOT NULL,
    latency INT NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE ProtocolMetrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    protocol_id INT NOT NULL,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL,
    latency_ms FLOAT,
    throughput Mbps FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE performance_metrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    protocol_id INT,
    device_id INT,
    latency_ms FLOAT,
    bandwidth_kbps INT,
    CONSTRAINT fk_protocol_id FOREIGN KEY (protocol_id) REFERENCES quantum_protocols(protocol_id),
    CONSTRAINT fk_device_id FOREIGN KEY (device_id) REFERENCES communication_devices(device_id)
);

CREATE TABLE ProtocolMetrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    protocol_id INT REFERENCES QuantumProtocols(protocol_id),
    latency INT,
    throughput FLOAT,
    success_rate FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE ExperimentResults (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    metric_id INT REFERENCES ProtocolMetrics(metric_id),
    experiment_date DATE,
    status VARCHAR(20),
    feedback TEXT
);
